nz.co.jedsimson.lgp.core.evolution.fitness

Class FitnessEvaluator<TData,TOutput extends Output<TData>,TTarget extends Target<? extends TData>>

  • nz.co.jedsimson.lgp.core.evolution.fitness.FitnessEvaluator<TData,TOutput,TTarget>
  • Type Parameters:
    TData -

    The type of the program being evaluated.

    TOutput -

    The type of output of the program being evaluated.

    TTarget -

    The type of target for fitness cases being evaluated against.


    public class FitnessEvaluator<TData,TOutput extends Output<TData>,TTarget extends Target<? extends TData>>

    Provides a way to evaluate the fitness of a program.

    This is done by using the class FitnessContext that is register with the interface EnvironmentFacade.

    See Also:
    class FitnessContext, interface EnvironmentFacade

        Performs an evaluation on program with the specified environment against the given dataset.

        The class FitnessEvaluator acts as a mediator between something that wants to know the fitness of a class Program and the actual class FitnessContext that fitness is calculated in.

        Parameters:
        program - The program to determine an evaluation for.
